Last month (and I believe this is common to all ALHs) the Tenants used by default in this course were changed.  W/the old Tenant I believe there were ~5 licenses not assigned at all.  In the new Tenant all licenses are pre-assigned to the users provided in that Tenant - with no extras to spare.   This leads to an issue of 'no licenses to assign' when one gets to this exer/task/step to assign one to the newly-created Holly user.  

I believe this also becomes an issue somewhat later in Mod2/Lab1/Exer1/Task 4 when we need another license to assign to the (previously local AD user) Abbie Parsons after she is imported into O365.

It seems like it might be a good idea to include some form of 'note' w/some additional steps at or before this portion of the lab instructions, describing the process of un-assigning at least 2 licenses from users that are not used in this course, such that there are licenses to spare when they are needed.

I believe  the users highlighted in yellow below (form the current Tenant) are not utilized at all in MS-500, and thus might be good users to use in any such 'unassign licenses' steps:

Last month (and I believe this is common to all ALHs) the Tenants used by default in this course were changed.  W/the old Tenant I believe there were ~5 licenses not assigned at all.  In the new Tenant all licenses are pre-assigned to the users provided in that Tenant - with no extras to spare.   This leads to an issue of 'no licenses to assign' when one gets to this exer/task/step to assign one to the newly-created Holly user.  

I believe this also becomes an issue somewhat later in Mod2/Lab1/Exer1/Task 4 when we need another license to assign to the (previously local AD user) Abbie Parsons after she is imported into O365.

It seems like it might be a good idea to include some form of 'note' w/some additional steps at or before this portion of the lab instructions, describing the process of un-assigning at least 2 licenses from users that are not used in this course, such that there are licenses to spare when they are needed.

I believe  the users highlighted in yellow below (form the current Tenant) are not utilized at all in MS-500, and thus might be good users to use in any such 'unassign licenses' steps:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49700217/135504655-9fcefc72-d51e-4b04-9914-5be60c622fb4.png)
